  "page": "Yandel",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Maester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/50px-Maester.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/75px-Maester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/100px-Maester.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Maester</span><br />Yandel</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Maester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/50px-Maester.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/75px-Maester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/100px-Maester.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_272_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">272&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Yandel</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>. He wrote the book <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Yandel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A foundling from his birth, left in an empty stall in the <a href=\"/index.php/Scribe%27s_Hearth\" title=\"Scribe&#39;s Hearth\">Scribe's Hearth</a> of the Citadel, Yandel was found by an <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters#Novices_and_Acolytes\" title=\"Maesters\">acolyte</a> who took him to the <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters#Seneschal\" title=\"Maesters\">Seneschal</a> of that year, <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Edgerran\" title=\"Edgerran\">Edgerran</a>. Edgerran announced that Yandel might prove of use, which when Yandel first heard the story, he believed to mean that Edgerran foresaw his destiny as a maester. It would be only later that Yandel would discover that Edgerran had been writing a treatise on the swaddling of infants at the time, and had wished to test certain theories.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Yandel was given to the care of servants, and received the occasional attention of maesters. He was raised as a servant amongst the halls, chambers, and libraries. Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Walgrave\" title=\"Walgrave\">Walgrave</a> taught him how to read and write. Yandel desired nothing more than to become one of the maesters. He wanted to read about faraway places and long-dead men, to gaze at the stars and measure the passing of the seasons. At the age of thirteen, in <a href=\"/index.php/285_AC\" title=\"285 AC\">285&#160;AC</a>, Yandel forged the first link of his chain, and other links would follow, until he completed his studies in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_292_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">292&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Having finished his studies, Yandel remained at the Citadel, serving the archmaesters and aiding them in all that they required. Meanwhile, he set about completing his work, <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Perestan\" title=\"Perestan\">Perestan</a> reminded Yandel that Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> was working on a history of the Targaryen kings, namely, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood, Being a History of the Targaryen Kings of Westeros\">Fire &amp; Blood, Being a History of the Targaryen Kings of Westeros</a></i>. Yandel persuaded Gyldayn to permit him to use fragments of the uncompleted <i>Fire &amp; Blood</i> in his <i>The World of Ice &amp; Fire</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Yandel dedicated <i>The World of Ice &amp; Fire</i> to King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>. Upon Robert's death, however, someone had his name replaced with <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey</a>'s and later <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen</a>'s. Yandel himself, for fear of angering the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a>, also cut out the vast majority of material on <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a>, and several others.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_scenes\">Behind the scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Yandel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the real-world book <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Yandel's words were written by <a href=\"/index.php/User:Ran\" title=\"User:Ran\">Elio Garcia</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/User:Linda\" title=\"User:Linda\">Linda Antonsson</a>, in the same way that anything attributed to Gyldayn was directly written by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-AMA_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-AMA-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the original texts, Yandel discovered a long but incomplete history of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> in the papers of Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_(archmaester)\" title=\"Gerold (archmaester)\">Gerold</a>, written by Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a>. Yandel used Gyldayn's work as a major source for his book <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, including a complete history of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>. He has discovered other manuscripts by Gyldayn, but many pages have been misplaced or destroyed, and still others have been damaged by neglect and by fire. Still, Yandel hopes that more pages will be found one day, and Gyldayn's <a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood, Being a History of the Targaryen Kings of Westeros\">lost masterwork</a> will be published, as the maesters of the Citadel are greatly excited by what Yandel has found so far.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>However, George R. R. Martin later decided to let Gyldayn live into <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>'s reign, so his history book could cover the entire Targaryen Dynasty.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gyldayn_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gyldayn-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Hence in latest prints, Gyldayn shared his uncompleted work with Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Perestan\" title=\"Perestan\">Perestan</a>, who then informed Yandel. And Yandel persuaded Gyldayn to permit the use of  passages from Gyldayn's work in Yandel's book.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Yandel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued3)#Yandel\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued3)\">Yandel</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafpreface.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Preface.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reign of the Dragons.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">r/asoiaf: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/asoiaf/comments/eyf4bc\">When did they update&#160;? (February 3, 2020)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/12432\">Stockholm and Archipelacon Report</a> (June 28, 2015)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-AMA-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-AMA_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">r/asoiaf: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/asoiaf/comments/2kgg2o/spoilers_all_ama_with_authors_of_the_world_of_ice/\">AMA with authors of The World of Ice and Fire, Elio García and Linda Antonsson! (Part 2 of 2)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Gyldayn-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Gyldayn_7-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">A Forum of Ice and Fire: FIRE AND BLOOD EXCERPT - <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php?/topic/152215-fire-and-blood-excerpt/&amp;do=findComment&amp;comment=8266072\">Gyldayn retcon (November 20, 2018)</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404000517\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.079 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.281 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 903/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10885/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 6841/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 999/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4524/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.44 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  267.278      1 -total\n 92.73%  247.837      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 92.00%  245.890      1 Template:Infobox\n  9.74%   26.023     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.56%   12.177      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  3.46%    9.238      6 Template:Ref\n  2.94%    7.849      3 Template:Date\n  2.09%    5.589      6 Template:Ref/core\n  1.58%    4.233      1 Template:References\n  0.32%    0.858      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:18388-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404000516 and revision id 321545\n -->\n",
